# -*- mode:org;coding:utf-8 -*-
#+TITLE: Implement sedit + aldo form-navigator integration (and fix the three nav bugs)
#+AUTHOR: Pascal J. Bourguignon

* Goal

Implement the =sedit= S-expression structural editor and its integration with
the *aldo* debugger's form navigator, per the specification, and fix the three
outstanding navigation bugs it references.

*Normative specification* (read it first, in full):
=clautolisp/documentation/clautolisp-sedit-spec.org= — "sedit and the aldo Form
Navigator". It is layered on, and does not restate:

- =clautolisp/documentation/clautolisp-debugger-tui-spec.org= (decorations,
  numbered poll-points, partial printing, the two navigators, the two stacks,
  stacked command dictionaries);
- =clautolisp/documentation/clautolisp-debugger-command-reference.org= (§0 the
  NORMATIVE command-naming rule; §3 Navigation; §8 dictionaries / settings).

*Bugs to fix* (they are prerequisites and good warm-ups):

- =issues/open/bug-aldo-duplicate-breakpoint.issue=
- =issues/open/bug-aldo-nav-command-dictionary.issue=
- =issues/open/bug-aldo-nav-entry-and-breakpoint-flow.issue=

*Related:* =clautolisp/documentation/clipboard-interface.org= (system clipboard);
=issues/open/aldo-pre-debug.issue= (=clal-nav-function= entry API).

* Branch and conventions

- Work on the *=sedit-nav= implementation branch* (off =master=). The =sedit=
  branch is *experimental* and is *not* the base — do not build on it. You may
  *read* its =sedit/sedit.lisp= / =dbgsim.lisp= as prior art, but the reference
  model is now §6 of the spec, not that code.
- Follow =AGENTS.md=. Common Lisp sources are LF + UTF-8.
- Naming ([[clautolisp_naming]] conventions): =clal-= prefix for the AutoLISP
  extension functions/commands (=clal-sedit=, =clal-nav-function=,
  =clal-clipboard-*=); =*clal-…*= for the AutoLISP-visible variables
  (=*clal-clipboard*=, =*clal-result*=, =*clal-sedit-initial-form*=, …). CL-side
  internals live in the existing =clautolisp.debug.*= / =clautolisp.ui.*=
  packages.
- *Version bump:* every change to clautolisp sources must bump =*version*= in
  =clautolisp/tools/clautolisp/source/version.lisp= (MAJOR.MINOR.DEVELOP —
  bump DEVELOP), and add a one-line entry to =RELEASE_NOTES.org=.
- Tests use =fiveam=, one =…/tests/= tree per ASDF system, with a =run.lisp=.
  Every new behaviour gets tests; the §6.7 invariants are the acceptance suite.

* Where the code lives (ground truth)

The debugger is already substantially built; NAV mode largely *exists*. Extend
it, do not restart.

| concern                              | system / file                                                        |
|--------------------------------------+----------------------------------------------------------------------|
| breakpoints (duplicate-bp bug)       | =clautolisp/autolisp-debug/source/breakpoints.lisp= (=add-breakpoint=)|
| poll-points / instrument / source↔instrumented | =autolisp-debug/source/{poll,instrument}.lisp=, =autolisp-source-map/= |
| *form navigator (NAV, non-mutating)* | =autolisp-debug-ui/source/navigator.lisp= (path-based; motions exist) |
| stacked command dictionaries         | =autolisp-debug-ui/source/command-table.lisp=                        |
| decorations / theme                  | =autolisp-debug-ui/source/decorations.lisp=                          |
| settings (=navigator=, add =sedit …=)| =autolisp-debug-ui/source/settings.lisp=                             |
| UI protocol / session                | =autolisp-debug-ui/source/{protocol,session}.lisp=                   |
| dumb-terminal UI + its tests         | =autolisp-debug-ui-dumb/=                                             |
| TUI screen protocol (ncurses/mock)   | =autolisp-debug-ui-tui/source/tui.lisp=                              |
| inspector (sibling mode dictionary)  | =autolisp-inspect/=                                                   |

New EDIT-mode editor code should live in its *own* system (e.g.
=clautolisp/autolisp-sedit=, =autolisp-sedit/source/{package,zipper,adorn,edit,
clipboard,fs,sedit}.lisp=) that =autolisp-debug-ui= depends on, so =sedit= is
reusable outside the debugger (=clal-sedit= at the REPL). Register it in
=clautolisp/clautolisp.asd= next to =autolisp-inspect=, with a
=…/autolisp-sedit/tests= system.

* Phase 0 — fix the three bugs (small, independently shippable)

1. *Duplicate breakpoint* (=bug-aldo-duplicate-breakpoint=). In
   =add-breakpoint= (and the =b= command path), make setting a breakpoint on a
   poll-point that already carries one *idempotent*: keep the single breakpoint
   (or report "breakpoint already set on ppN"); never append, never double the
   glyph. Test: two =b= on the same selection ⇒ one breakpoint, one decoration.

2. *Nav command dictionary* (=bug-aldo-nav-command-dictionary=). Make navigation
   mode actually *stack* the navigator dictionary over the global debugger
   dictionary (=command-table.lisp=), so all non-shadowed debugger verbs are
   directly reachable in NAV; derive the =?= help line from the *union* of the
   active dictionaries, not a literal. Test: from NAV, =c i n o a r j b bo f
   fi… p t v l*= dispatch; =?= lists them.

3. *Nav entry + breakpoint flow* (=bug-aldo-nav-entry-and-breakpoint-flow=).
   (a) On entering the form navigator on a form, the initial selection is the
   *first poll-point* (=nav-down= of the whole form, §4/§6.4-skip), not the
   whole =defun=. (b) Provide =clal-nav-function= (see =aldo-pre-debug.issue=)
   so a breakpoint can be placed *without* first faking a break, and hide the
   =clal-invoke-debugger= synthetic toplevel poll-point in that flow. Tests:
   entry selection = first pp; =clal-nav-function= opens NAV with no fake stop.

* Phase 1 — sedit core (EDIT mode): the zipper (spec §6.1–§6.3)

- Adorned-tree domain (§6.1): =Atom / List α / Comment α / File / Dir=, with
  adornment =α= (newlines, attached comments, column info) separate from
  structure.
- The Huet zipper =Loc = (t, C)= (§6.2): =down up right left first last skip=,
  O(1), structure-sharing, with the *level tag* advancing across sexp→form→
  file→dir boundaries.
- Editing transitions (§6.3): =insert add replace=, =copy cut paste=, and the
  structural =wrap slurp barf splice split join=; each selects its result; a
  form-level mutation inside a =File= marks it modified.
- Property tests from §6.7: split/join, wrap/splice, slurp/barf round-trips;
  motion totality/inverse.

* Phase 2 — undo (spec §6.4)

- Add the single =undo-save= slot =Empty | Saved op Loc=. *Record* the
  descriptor + pre-mutation =Loc= before each mutation of §6.3; leave it
  untouched on non-mutating commands. *Restore* by the *swap* rule so =undo= is
  self-inverse (second =undo= = redo). Tests: the §6.7 "undo restores, and is
  self-inverse" invariant, incl. navigation between mutation and undo, and
  file-modified-marker recomputation after a swap.

* Phase 3 — adornment, formatting, comments (spec §5.2–§5.3, §5.8)

- Pretty-printer that, given =sexp + NEWLINES + indent rules=, reproduces the
  source =TEXT= (§6.7 formatting fidelity). AutoLISP has a finite special-
  operator set, so indentation is fully determined; comments indent by level
  (=;-= column / =;;-= subform / =;;;- ;;;;-= flush-left; =;| |;= blocks).
- Comment objects, contiguous-comment merging, and deferral of multi-line
  comment *text* editing to =$VISUAL=/=$EDITOR= (a =set= option).

* Phase 4 — =clal-sedit=, storage, REPL recording (spec §2, §3, §5.7–§5.9)

- =clal-sedit [object]= entry points: =nil= (stand-alone), a sexp, a symbol
  (recall its recorded/File form), a *file path*, a *directory path*; the
  initial-selection / final-selection / result table (§2) and
  =*clal-sedit-initial-form*= / =*clal-sedit-last-result*=.
- REPL source recording (§3): the *definition dictionary* (name→form, from
  =setq/defun/defun-q=) and the ordered *session log* (all toplevel forms);
  =clal-sedit 'NAME= recalls; re-eval updates.
- Filesystem level (§5.9): =new rename delete=, minimalist directory nav.
- =save= + =load= (§5.7–§5.8): =save=-on-leave with the =set sedit auto-saving
  sexp|file|disable= setting and the confirmation prompts; =load [FILE]= (=l=),
  in both modes, re-installing edited definitions.

* Phase 5 — modes, transitions, and aldo integration (spec §1, §5, §7)

- The revised command set and keys (spec §5 table), registered *per dictionary*
  through =command-table.lisp='s registrar (which enforces §0). Note the
  reassignments: =next/prev→forward/backward= (=> <=), old =enlist→wrap=, =l=
  is now =load=, CUA =x c v= as conventional clipboard keys, =z= undo,
  =ic/ac/rc= comment variants, dir =r=/=x=/=n= object-exclusive.
- The *two modes* and the transition machine (§1.3, §6.6): editing command (by
  *word*) or =edit= switches NAV→EDIT; =debug CMD= / =aldo CMD= (synonyms) or
  =nav= returns to NAV; =load= changes neither. In EDIT the debugger dict is
  reached only through the =debug=/=aldo= prefix.
- Integration (§7): =clal-nav-function= opens NAV at the first poll-point;
  re-entry re-anchors to the current poll-point; editing a function then
  =save=+=load= installs the new definition, breakpoints carrying over by
  poll-point identity; =set navigator sexp|line= selects the presentation
  (the =line= navigator is the flat alternative, mostly already present).

* Phase 6 — clipboard (spec §5.4 + clipboard-interface.org)

- Editor-facing lisp clipboard =*clal-clipboard*= with adorned =(SEXP …)= /
  =(COMMENT …)= objects; =clal-clipboard-{put,get}-text= /
  =clal-clipboard-{copy,paste}-sexp=.
- The system-clipboard *provider* layer (X11/Wayland/macOS/Windows/OSC52/NULL),
  serialization, and security exactly per =clipboard-interface.org= (that
  document is normative for this phase). Degrade to =:NULL= with no build deps.

* Acceptance

- The three bug tests pass, and the behaviours are visible in the dumb UI.
- The §6.7 invariants are encoded as fiveam tests and green:
  motion totality/inverse, split/join & wrap/splice & slurp/barf round-trips,
  idempotent designation (+ idempotent breakpoint), undo restores & is
  self-inverse, mode preservation, formatting fidelity.
- =clal-sedit= works at the REPL for all §2 argument kinds; a =load=/=save=
  round trip on clean source is byte-preserving.
- In the debugger: enter NAV at the first poll-point, all debugger verbs reach
  directly; edit a function (NAV→EDIT), =save=, =load=, =aldo continue= (→NAV),
  and the new definition runs at the next call.
- Docs kept in sync: bump the sedit spec version for any spec change made while
  implementing; note the work in =RELEASE_NOTES.org=; update the debugger
  implementation-plan org if module boundaries shift.

* Suggested order

Phase 0 (ship the bug fixes) → 1 → 2 → 3 → 4 → 5 → 6. Each phase is testable on
its own; keep commits small and the version bumped per change.

* STATUS

** 2026-07-05 — Phase 0 DONE (clautolisp 1.4.15, branch =sedit-nav=)

All three prerequisite bugs are fixed, tested, and verified end-to-end in the
built binary; the =bug-aldo-*= tickets can be closed.

1. *Duplicate breakpoint* (=bug-aldo-duplicate-breakpoint=). =add-breakpoint=
   (autolisp-debug/breakpoints.lisp) is now idempotent for a *plain* breakpoint
   (steady, no condition/action): it returns =(values BP NEW-P)= and reuses the
   existing breakpoint on a poll-point that already carries one — no duplicate,
   no doubled glyph. =cmd-set-breakpoint= propagates NEW-P; the =b= paths report
   "already set". Conditioned/action/volatile breakpoints are still distinct.

2. *Nav command dictionary* (=bug-aldo-nav-command-dictionary=). In the =:sexp=
   navigator the motion keys (=d u > < << >> ±N=, spec §5) are handled first and
   every other token falls through to =run-command= (the global debugger
   dispatch): =c i n o a r j=, the breakpoint/frame/inspection verbs, etc. are
   reachable bare; a resume directive (continue/step) leaves NAV carrying it up.
   =?= prints the motion keys *and* the debugger help. The colliding letter
   aliases =i k jj j l ll= were retired (they shadowed =into=/=jump=/=list-locals=).

3. *Nav entry + breakpoint flow* (=bug-aldo-nav-entry-and-breakpoint-flow=).
   (a) =nav-function-loc= descends to the *first poll-point* on entry (nav-down
   of the whole form), not the whole =defun=. (b) =(clal-nav-function 'NAME)= at
   the REPL opens the navigator *without a fake break*: =request-nav= gains
   =*defer-nav-request*= (bound by the REPL turn) so it only queues; the REPL
   drains the request after the turn via the new UI generic
   =ui-open-navigation-request=, resolving NAME in the session context. No
   synthetic toplevel poll-point is shown.

Tests: autolisp-debug 122/122, autolisp-debug-ui-dumb 390/390, emacs 27/27,
ncurses 42/42.

** 2026-07-05 — Phase 1 DONE (clautolisp 1.4.16, branch =sedit-nav=)

The =sedit= core is implemented as a new, dependency-free system
=clautolisp/autolisp-sedit= (registered next to =autolisp-inspect=; its
=…/tests= system too), so it is reusable outside the debugger. Package
=clautolisp.sedit=. Contents:

- *Adorned-tree domain* (§6.1): =atom-node / list-node / comment-node /
  file-node / dir-node=, each carrying an opaque adornment =α= (Phase 3 fills
  it). Uniform =branch-node-p / node-children / node-with-children
  (=PLATE) / node-level-of-children=, plus =sexp->tree= / =tree->sexp=.
- *The Huet zipper* (§6.2): =loc = (focus, ctx)=; motions =loc-down/up/left/
  right/first/last/skip=, O(1) and structure-sharing; =right= past the last
  sibling and =left= before the first *ascend*, while =first/last/skip= stay at
  the level and clamp. Level tag (=:sexp/:form/:file/:root=) derived from the
  parent; =loc-root / loc-path / loc-follow=.
- *Editing transitions* (§6.3): =edit-insert/add/replace/delete= and the
  structural =edit-wrap/splice/slurp/barf/split/join=; each selects its result.
  A mutation inside a =File= marks it modified (walks to the nearest enclosing
  file-node, rebuilding only that spine). Editor state =sedit-state= (loc + clip
  + mode) with =sedit-copy/cut/paste=.

Tests (=autolisp-sedit/tests=, *95/95*): the §6.7 invariants — motion totality
within a form, down/up and right/left inverse, and the =wrap↔splice=,
=slurp↔barf=, =split↔join= round-trips — plus level tags, path round-trip,
selection-after-mutation, and file-modified marking.

Deferred: Phase 2 undo (§6.4, the one-slot swap), Phase 3 adornment/pretty-
printer (§5.2–§5.3), Phase 4 =clal-sedit= + REPL recording (§2–§3), Phase 5
modes/aldo integration (§1/§7 — this is where =autolisp-debug-ui= gains the
=autolisp-sedit= dependency), Phase 6 clipboard providers (§5.4 +
=clipboard-interface.org=).
